<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-9631] The OsgiServiceRegistry class caches service references</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-9631</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As discussed in &lt;a href=&quot;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/OsgiServiceRegistry-caching-service-references-why-td5777410.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://camel.465427.n5.nabble.com/OsgiServiceRegistry-caching-service-references-why-td5777410.html&lt;/a&gt; the OsgiServiceRegistry class caches service references hence limits the ability to dynamically install and use a new version of the same service&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12940942">CAMEL-9631</key>
            <summary>The OsgiServiceRegistry class caches service references</summary>
